Amgen - Wikipedia






















 






Amgen

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Amgen Inc.





Amgen headquarters in Thousand Oaks, California




Formerly called

Applied Molecular Genetics
(1980–1983)



Type

Public


Traded as
NASDAQ: AMGN
NASDAQ-100 Component
S&P 100 Component
S&P 500 Component
SEHK: 4332


Industry
Biotechnology


Founded
1980


Headquarters
Thousand Oaks, California, U.S.



Key people

Robert A. Bradway
(Chairman, President, and CEO)


Products
Epogen, Aranesp, Kineret, Enbrel, Neulasta, Neupogen, Nplate, Vectibix, Prolia, Xgeva, and Sensipar/Mimpara.


Revenue
